The paper focuses on optimizing the structure and connection weights of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also applies the proposed method to fully-connected and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of gradient methods and stochastic gradient descent, which are common optimization techniques in neural networks, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the control of model complexity, which is a topic in control theory and systems engineering, suggesting that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
